'''Abyssal Space'''{{CiteText|text=Abyssal book|quote=Despite having finally gained access to the strange dimension known as the Abyss (also referred to as Abyssal Space or the Abyssal Plane), we have found the area to still be something of an enigma.}}, often simply referred to as the '''Abyss''', is a plane that sits between and around [[planes]].{{CiteNPC|npc=Mage of Zamorak|quote=It is a hard place to describe. We often refer to it as another plane, but that isn't quite accurate. If anything, it is more like a plane that sits between all other planes.}} Its relationship to other planes is described as that of a {{WP|tesseract}} or hypercube,{{CiteText|text=Abyssal book|quote=...the Abyss is somewhat of a tesseract or hypercube with a direct relation to our dimension.}} and is mostly known for being the primary medium for teleportation magic and inter-planar travel.{{CiteNPC|npc=Mage of Zamorak|quote=It [the Abyss] can be used as an effective hub for teleportation. In fact, all teleportation that we know of uses the Abyss, you just don't realise it.}}{{CiteNPC|npc=Mage of Zamorak|quote=Whenever you use a teleport spell, that spell is actually travelling through the Abyss and using it to link two places together.}}

The Abyss is described as a 'glue' that holds all planes together, yet separate,{{CiteText|text=Abyssal book|quote=The Abyss seems to be a strange dimension that sits between all other planes. In some ways, the Abyss acts as a 'glue' that holds all planes together, yet keeps them separate, if you will.}} and as a result exists at the 'fringe' of reality,{{CiteText|text=Abyssal book|quote=...the Abyss exists at the 'fringe' of reality, meaning that it does not conform to the same guidelines of space and time observed on Gielinor, or indeed on other planes.}} where it defies the laws of time and space that apply on other planes.{{CiteNPC|npc=Mage of Zamorak|quote=You see, time and space work differently in the Abyss. For example, you can travel to the Abyss, walk a few steps and then exit, only to find yourself somewhere completely different from where you entered. You might even find yourself on a different plane. You can also enter the Abyss and spend days there, but on your return, only moments have passed.}}{{CiteText|text=Overseer's book|quote=Although time does not pass in the Abyss at the same rate that it passes elsewhere, I have been imprisoned for an unimaginably long time, since the days when the gods fought for dominion of the mortal realm.}} While teleportation spells make use of the Abyss, teleporting directly to it is difficult to do intentionally,{{CiteText|text=Abyssal book|quote=...our gaining access to the Abyss was somewhat of a fluke, and a not easily repeatable fluke at that. Due to the Abyss not being a plane in the traditional sense, we have also had to resort to unusual measures to gain permanent access.}} and leaving it also appears to be difficult without sufficient teleportation energy.{{CiteNPC|npc=The Overseer|quote=We broke through to the Abyss, seeking allies for our cause, but instead I ended up a prisoner in this place, unable to leave, while the God Wars continued without me.}}{{CiteNPC|npc=The Overseer|quote=Bringing me those body parts from the Sires has now granted me enough teleportation energy to leave this living hell hole.}}

Proper access to the Abyss was recently established by the [[Zamorak Magical Institute]] after an accidental teleportation failure,{{CiteText|text=Abyssal book|quote=...it was only recently that we finally discovered a way to enter this strange realm. The discovery came by complete chance, when a routine teleportation experiment seemingly went wrong.}} and was accomplished by an [[Dark Mage (Abyss)|initiate]] purposely "failing" a teleport spell and arriving at the Abyss, who then cast a portal spell to establish a link between Gielinor and the Abyss.{{CiteText|text=Abyssal book|quote=We then had them [initiates] repeatedly teleport to various locations, seeking to replicate the original error that caused the first entry into the Abyss. Once one of our initiates had managed to 'fail' his teleport and appear in the Abyss he was then charged with remaining there and holding a portal spell open so that more senior members of the Z.M.I. could gain entry.}}{{CiteNPC|npc=Dark Mage (Abyss){{!}}Dark Mage|quote=By remaining here and holding this rift open, I am providing a permanent link between normal space and this strange dimension. As long as my spell remains in effect, we have the capability to teleport into the Abyss.}} Despite this, there are other means of permanent access to other parts of the Abyss, such as the [[fairy ring]] network.

==Areas==
There are several areas of Abyssal Space that the player can currently access.

===Runic Rifts===
{{Main|Abyss}}

The part of the Abyss that the [[Zamorak Magical Institute]] accesses to teleport directly to the temples housing the [[runic altar]]s. The outer ring is accessed via the [[Mage of Zamorak]], though aggressive abyssal creatures will attack players upon arrival.

The inner ring contains the rifts that accesses the runic altars, and the [[Dark Mage (Abyss)|Z.M.I. initiate]] maintaining the connection that allows teleportation into this area of the Abyss is found here as well.

===Abyssal Area===
{{Main|Abyssal Area}}

A part of the Abyss that can only be accessed by using the code {{Fairycode|ALR}} in the [[fairy rings]] network. Uniquely, [[abyssal demon]]s can be found in this section of the Abyss alongside other abyssal creatures.

===Abyssal Nexus===
{{Main|Abyssal Nexus}}

A part of the Abyss occupied by [[Abyssal Sire]]s, extremely dangerous demons who constructed the Nexus to sustain themselves. [[The Overseer]], who broke through the Abyss in search of allies during the [[God Wars]], became trapped here due to a lack of teleportation energy.

===The Scar===
{{Main|The Scar}}

Currently inaccessible by players, the Scar is supposedly the most dangerous part of the Abyss. A rift to the Scar was once sealed off in the [[Temple of the Eye (location)|Temple of the Eye]], but has reopened and must be periodically closed by the [[Guardians of the Rift]].

